## About The Project

### Problem Statement

üéØ A telecommunications company in California was facing a challenge with customer retention. The primary goal was to leverage customer data to build a predictive model that could accurately identify customers at a high risk of churning, allowing the company to proactively take measures to retain them.

### Dataset

üìä The dataset used for this analysis is `telecom_customer_churn.csv`, which contains information on 7,043 customers across California. It includes customer demographics, account information, subscribed services, and monthly/total charges.

### Built With

This project was built using the following technologies and libraries:

* **Programming Language:** [Python](https://www.python.org/)
* **Data Analysis:** [Pandas](https://pandas.pydata.org/), [NumPy](https://numpy.org/)
* **Data Visualization:** [Plotly](https://plotly.com/)
* **Machine Learning:** [Scikit-learn](https://scikit-learn.org/), [XGBoost](https://xgboost.ai/)

