## Results & Conclusion

‚ú® The final model, an **XGBoost Classifier**, proved to be the most effective for this prediction task.

üèÜ **Final Model Accuracy: 80.86%**

The model's performance is detailed in the confusion matrix, which shows its ability to correctly distinguish between customers who churned and those who stayed. This model can be a valuable tool for the company to identify at-risk customers and implement targeted retention strategies, ultimately reducing revenue loss.

